article.headline: Bucknell 78, Army 64
article.story: LEWISBURG, Pa. -- Bryan Cohen scored 12 points and Mike Muscala added 11 points and 10 rebounds as Bucknell defeated Army 78-64 on Saturday in the regular-season finale for both teams. The Bison (22-8, 13-1 Patriot League) shot just 9 for 24 from the field (37.5 percent) in the opening half but still held a 30-22 advantage at the break, thanks to a dismal shooting effort by the Black Knights. Army (11-18, 3-11) missed 15 of its first 16 field goal attempts and both of its first two free throws. Jeremy Hence ended both droughts at the 8:37 mark of the first half with a three-point play that pulled the Black Knights to 12-5. Hence finished with 26 points and Ella Ellis added 22 for Army, which has lost seven straight and 10 of 11. Bryson Johnson and Cameron Ayers each scored 11 points for Bucknell, which has lost only one time since Dec. 22 -- a 90-70 blowout loss to Army on Jan. 29.
